Overview

There are approximately 114,000 children under 18 living in Monterey County. That is 26.4% of the population (ACS 2017 DP05). Of them, 21.6% live in poverty (ACS 2017 DP03).

Demographics

Monterey County students represent a diversity of backgrounds.

There are approximately 8,882.00 migrant students EiP in Monterey County. This is 11.39% of enrolled students compared with 1.41% for California. For Monterey County, approximately 31.45% are Non-Attending, and Non-Attending students are primarily aged 17 and older.
